The paper deals with designing codes for an erasure channel with additive noise, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of low rank lattice codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) due to the consideration of power constraints and erasure patterns.
